NIGERIAN gospel singer Adora Nkiru aka Ada Jesus has revealed plans to release her latest music single ‘Obinigwe’.   Edochie’s first wife shrugs off marriage drama     Faze, Konga, others thrill at Ruggedman’s Foundation night     Adaorah shines at BET awards   Ada Jesus, in a chat with The Nation, recalled her journey into the music industry saying, “I’m naturally a music person right from my tender age, so music is me and I am music. What inspires me is my passion for the things of God. Winning more souls for Him. These things come to me naturally.” On her latest single, she said, “My first music project was Passion for Christ, then another single titled No Be Say I Dey Craze, then Obinigwe. The song is full praise to God for all the gifts we keep receiving from Him. Obinigwe means God in Heaven and the song’s title speaks more for itself.”